{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id053cba9b-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1450"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1450"},"text":"§ 1450.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Unlading on Sundays, holidays, or during overtime hours","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"No merchandise, baggage, or passengers arriving in the United States from any foreign port or place, and no bonded merchandise or baggage being transported from one port to another, shall be unladen from the carrying aircraft, vessel or vehicle on Sunday, a holiday, or during overtime hours, except under special license granted by the appropriate customs officer under such regulations as the Secretary of the Treasury may prescribe.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id053cba9c-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1930-06-17/ch497"},"text":"June 17, 1930, ch. 497","children":[],"tail":", title IV, § 450, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/46/715"},"text":"46 Stat. 715","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271/tIII/s301/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–271, title III, § 301(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-06-02"},"text":"June 2, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/287"},"text":"84 Stat. 287","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/66/tXIII/s13811/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–66, title XIII, § 13811(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/670"},"text":"107 Stat. 670","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id053cba9d-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id053cba9e-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id053cba9f-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions similar to those in this section were contained in R.S. § 2872, as amended by the ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1884-06-26/ch121/s25"},"text":"act of June 26, 1884, ch. 121, § 25","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/23/59"},"text":"23 Stat. 59","children":[],"tail":", which was superseded by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1922-09-21/ch356/tIV/s450"},"text":"act Sept. 21, 1922, ch. 356, title IV, § 450","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/954"},"text":"42 Stat. 954","children":[],"tail":", and was repealed by section 642 thereof. Section 450 of the 1922 act was superseded by section 450 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1930-06-17"},"text":"June 17, 1930","children":[],"tail":", comprising this section, and repealed by section 651(a)(1) of the 1930 act."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"R.S. § 2871 providing for the granting of a special license to unlade at night, and the amendment thereof by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1906-06-30/ch3909"},"text":"act June 30, 1906, ch. 3909","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/34/633"},"text":"34 Stat. 633","children":[],"tail":", were repealed by section 6 of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1911-02-13/ch46"},"text":"act Feb. 13, 1911, ch. 46","children":[],"tail":", and provision for the grant of 